= section "Weak Roots in Scale VI" do
  = section "C1 = Ř" do
    %p Root-initial *Ř, as in #{t "νιστυρ̄σώβ", "nistuřsāb"} “come to be thought, be widely thought” (*řsāb “think”), is regular.

  = section "C2 = Ř" do
    %p Root-medial *Ř, as in #{t "νίστυβρ̄ώθ", "nistubřāṯ"} “be diversified, have varying results, come to be mixed” (*břāṯ “mix”), is regular.

  = section "C3 = Ř" do
    %p Root-final *Ř affects the feminine suffix *-ī in the present tense and imperative, which becomes *-ēyi. The passive verb #{t "νιστυφτώρ̄", "nistuftāř"} “open up, become attainable (opportunities, goals, etc)” (*ftāř “open”), for instance, has the form #{t "ιωστυφταρ̄ήι", "yāstuftařēyi"} “it (f) is opening up/becoming attainable” instead of regular **yāstuftařī. In addition, the last vowel of the active participle is lowered to /e/.

  = section "C1 = '/H" do
    %p Root-initial *' and *H behave identically, surfacing as /h/ in all forms for both <i>staktab</i> and <i>nistuktāb</i>, followed by an epenthetic /a/ to prevent an illegal consonant cluster. The root *'kāl “eat”, for instance, gives the verbs #{t "στάηακαλ", "stahakal"} “feed oneself, nourish oneself” (not **sta'kal) and #{t "νιστυηακώλ", "nistuhakāl"} “be fed [to]” (not **nistu'kāl).

  = section "C2 = '/H" do
    %p Root-internal *' and *H always assimilate into #{template "C1"}, resulting in gemination or aspiration. If aspiration appears, any preceding short vowel will in turn reduce to schwa, as in the Scale VI derivatives of *k'āb “hurt, be painful”, #{t "στάκκαβ", "stəkhab"} “hurt oneself” (not **stak'ab) and #{t "νιστακκώβ", "nistəkhāb"} “start to hurt, become increasingly painful” (not **nistuk'āb).

  = section "C3 = '" do
    %p Root-final *' has the same erratic behavior as in other scales. In most forms it drops when word-final and is preserved elsewhere, except in the two past tenses, where a special set of endings are used. Examples include the active verb #{t "στάλδα", "stalda"} “pull oneself up” (*ldā' “rise, go up”) and the passive verb #{t "νιστυβρώ", "nistubrā"} “come to be clear, become increasingly clear” (*brī' “clear”), the first of which is demonstrated below.
    - alashian = { :present     => %w(άσταλδα τίσταλδα τισταλδαεί ίσταλδα ισταλδαεί νισταλδαού τισταλδαού τισταλδαού ισταλδαού),
                   :preterite   => %w(στάλδωτ στάλδαττα στάλδατζζε στάλδα σταλδαώ σταλδαννώ στάλδαττυν στάλδατζζιν σταλδαού),
                   :imperfect   => %w(σταλδιή σταλδιήτ σταλδιής̄ σταλδιή σταλδιηώ σταλδιήν σταλδιήττυν σταλδιήτζζιν σταλδιηού),
                   :subjunctive => %w(в̄ώσταλδα в̄ετίσταλδα в̄ετίσταλδα в̄ήσταλδα в̄ήσταλδα в̄ενίσταλδα в̄ετίσταλδα в̄ετίσταλδα в̄ήσταλδα),
                   :imperative  => %w(έσταλδα εσταλδαεί εσταλδαού),
                   :infinitive  => "μάσταλδα",
                   :participle  => "μύσταλδι" }
    - latin = { :present     => %w('astalda tistalda tistalda'ī yistalda yistalda'ī nistalda'ū tistalda'ū tistalda'ū yistalda'ū),
                :preterite   => %w(staldāt staldətha staldəčhe stalda stalda'ā staldnannā staldəthun staldəčhin stalda'ū),
                :imperfect   => %w(staldie staldiet staldieš staldie staldie'ā staldien staldiethun staldiečhin staldie'ū),
                :subjunctive => %w(vāstalda vetistalda vetistalda vēstalda vēstalda vetistalda vetistalda vetistalda vēstalda),
                :imperative  => %w('estalda 'estalda'ī 'estalda'ū),
                :infinitive  => "mastalda",
                :participle  => "mustaldi" }
    = render 'full_conjugation_table', :title => "Scale VI Conjugation", :verb => { :ala => "stalda", :eng => "pull oneself up" }, :alashian => alashian, :latin => latin

  = section "C3 = H" do
    %p Roots with final *H lose this radical and conjugate as though they were biconsonantal, with inherent vowel *ā. The root *zgāh “mad, crazy”, for instance, behaves as though it were *zāg, giving the verb #{t "σταζώγ", "stazāg"} “drive oneself mad”. These then follow a regular biconsonantal paradigm.

  = section "C1 = Y/W" do
    %p Root-initial *Y and *W undergo monophthongization in all forms, according to the patterns *ay → *ē, *aw → *ū, uy → *ū, *uw → *ū. This new long vowel does not affect stress. Shown below is the present and preterite conjugation of #{t "στούκκαδ", "stūkhad"} “burn oneself” (*wkhād “burn”)#{footnote}.
    %table.invisible
      %tr
        - alashian = %w(άστουκκαδ τίστουκκαδ τιστουκκαδεί ίστουκκαδ ιστουκκαδεί νιστουκκαδού τιστουκκαδού τιστουκκαδού ίστουκκαδού ιστουκκαδού)
        - latin = %w('astūkhad tistūkhad tistūkhadī yistūkhad yistūkhadī nistūkhadū tistūkhadū tistūkhadū yistūkhadū yistūkhadū)
        %td= render 'verb_table', :title => "Scale VI Present Tense", :verb => { :ala => "stūkhad", :eng => "burn oneself" }, :alashian => alashian, :latin => latin
        - alashian = %w(στούκκαδετ στούκκαδ̄τα στούκκαδ̄σ̄ε στούκκαδ στουκκαδώ στουκκαδνώ στούκκαδ̄τυν στούκκαδ̄σ̄ιν στουκκαδού στουκκαδού)
        - latin = %w(stūkhadet stūkhaḏta stūkhaḏše stūkhad stūkhadā stūkhadnā stūkhaḏtun stūkhaḏšin stūkhadū stūkhadū)
        %td= render 'verb_table', :title => "Scale VI Preterite Tense", :verb => { :ala => "stūkhad", :eng => "burn oneself" }, :alashian => alashian, :latin => latin

  = section "C3 = Y/W" do
    %p The behavior of root-final *Y and *W in Scale VI varies depending on their environment. Intervocalically, they are completely regular. In coda position, they monophthongize if after a short vowel (*ay → *ē, *aw → *ū, *iy → *ī, *iw → *ī) or simply drop if after a long vowel or diphthong. They also drop in most forms of the imperfect. Monophthongization does not impact stress. Two examples are the active verbs #{t "στάμνου", "stamnū"} “account, take records” (*mnāw “count”) and #{t "στάρτζη", "starčē"} “covet” (*rčhīy “like, enjoy, be pleased by”, originally “want”), the latter shown in full below.
    - alashian = { :present     => %w(άσταρτζη τίσταρτζη τισταρτζαιεί ίσταρτζη ισταρτζαιεί νισταρτζαιού τισταρτζαιού τισταρτζαιού ισταρτζαιού),
                   :preterite   => %w(στάρτζαιετ στάρτζητα στάρτζησ̄ε στάρτζη σταλδαώ σταρτζηνώ στάρτζητυν στάρτζησ̄ιν σταρτζαιού),
                   :imperfect   => %w(σταρτζιή σταρτζιήτ σταρτζιής̄ σταρτζιή σταρτζιηιώ σταρτζιήν σταρτζιήτυν σταρτζιήσ̄ιν σταρτζιηιού),
                   :subjunctive => %w(в̄ώσταρτζη в̄ετίσταρτζη в̄ετίσταρτζη в̄ήσταρτζη в̄ήσταρτζη в̄ενίσταρτζη в̄ετίσταρτζη в̄ετίσταρτζη в̄ήσταρτζη),
                   :imperative  => %w(έσταρτζη εσταρτζαιεί εσταρτζαιού),
                   :infinitive  => "μάσταρτζη",
                   :participle  => "μύσταρτζει" }
    - latin = { :present     => %w('astarčē tistarčē tistarčayī yistarčē yistarčayī nistarčayū tistarčayū tistarčayū yistarčayū),
                :preterite   => %w(starčayet starčēta starčēše starčē starčayā starčēnā starčētun starčēšin starčayū),
                :imperfect   => %w(starčie starčiet starčieš starčie starčieyā starčien starčietun starčiešin starčieyū),
                :subjunctive => %w(vāstarčē vetistarčē vetistarčē vēstarčē vēstarčē vetistarčē vetistarčē vetistarčē vēstarčē),
                :imperative  => %w('estarčē 'estarčayī 'estarčayū),
                :infinitive  => "mastarčē",
                :participle  => "mustarčī" }
    = render 'full_conjugation_table', :title => "Scale VI Conjugation", :verb => { :ala => "starčē", :eng => "covet" }, :alashian => alashian, :latin => latin

  = section "C1/C2/C3 = N" do
    %p Root-initial *N, as in #{t "στάφφας", "staffas"} “breathe heavily, hyperventilate” (*nfās “breathe”), always undergoes assimilation into the following #{template "C2"}, resulting in gemination or aspiration. If aspiration appears, any immediately preceding short vowel will reduce to schwa.
    %p Root-internal *N, as in #{t "νιστυγνώβ", "nistugnāb"} “be impressive, amazing (coll.)” (*gnāb “steal”), is regular.
    %p Root-final *N is irregular only in the two past tenses, where assimilation takes place in a number of forms. With the root *šfān “cover” we get the verb #{t "νιστυσ̄φών", "nistušfān"} “admit”:
    %table.invisible
      %tr
        - alashian = %w(νιστυσ̄φώνετ νιστυσ̄φώττα νιστυσ̄φώτζζε νιστυσ̄φών νιστυσ̄φωνώ νιστυσ̄φωννώ νιστυσ̄φώττυν νιστυσ̄αώτζζιν νιστυσ̄φωνού νιστυσ̄φωνού)
        - latin = %w(nistušfānet nistušfātha nistušfāčhe nistušfān nistušfānā nistušfānnā nistušfāthun nistušfāčhin nistušfānū nistušfānū)
        %td= render 'verb_table', :title => "Scale VI Preterite Tense", :verb => { :ala => "nistušfān", :eng => "admit" }, :alashian => alashian, :latin => latin
        - alashian = %w(νιστυσ̄φυώ νιστυσ̄φυώτ νιστυσ̄φυώς̄ νιστυσ̄φυών νιστυσ̄φυωνώ νιστυσ̄φυών νιστυσ̄φυώττυν νιστυσ̄φυώτζζιν νιστυσ̄φυωνού νιστυσ̄φυωνού)
        - latin = %w(nistušfuo nistušfuot nistušfuoš nistušfuon nistušfuonā nistušfuon nistušfuothun nistušfuočhin nistušfuonū nistušfuonū)
        %td= render 'verb_table', :title => "Scale VI Imperfect Tense", :verb => { :ala => "nistušfān", :eng => "admit" }, :alashian => alashian, :latin => latin

  = section "C1 = PH/TH/KH/TSH/ČH" do
    %p Roots with initial aspirates are largely unproblematic. Since #{template "C1"} is always in a cluster, it will always surface in an unaspirated state. The only difference between this and the regular paradigms is that any short vowel immediately preceding #{template "C1"} will reduce to /ə/. One such root is *khbāl “agree”, giving the verb #{t "στάκβαλ", "stəkbal"} “convince oneself”.

  = section "C2 = PH/TH/KH/TSH/ČH" do
    %p Root-internal aspirates will always surface in their unaspirated form and do not have any additional effects. These roots are for all intents and purposes regular.

  = section "C3 = PH/TH/KH/TSH/ČH" do
    %p #{template "C3"} aspirates have the same sorts of effects as in other scales. They cause preceding short vowels to reduce to schwa and trigger a special set of endings in the past tenses, which include an epenthetic vowel in some forms. Aspiration only surfaces when the consonant is intervocal. Shown below is the full conjugation of the verb #{t "νιστυσλώτ", "nistuslāt"} “be defeated, vanquished (poet.)” (*slāth “prevail over”):
    - alashian = { :present     => %w(ωστυσλώτ τωστυσλώτ τωστυσλαττεί ιωστυσλώτ ιωστυσλαττεί νωστυσλαττού τωστυσλαττού τωστυσλαττού ιωστυσλαττού),
                   :preterite   => %w(νιστυσλώττετ νιστυσλώτταττα νιστυσλώττατζζε νιστυσλώτ νιστυσλωττώ νιστυσλωτνώ νιστυσλώτταττυν νιστυσλώττατζζιν νιστυσλωττού),
                   :imperfect   => %w(νιστυσλυώτ νιστυσλυώττατ νιστυσλυώττας̄ νιστυσλυώτ νιστυσλυωττώ νιστυσλυώτταν νιστυσλυώτταττυν νιστυσλυώττατζζιν νιστυσλυωττού),
                   :subjunctive => %w(в̄ώστυσλατ в̄ατώστυσλατ в̄ατώστυσλατ в̄ιώστυσλατ в̄ιώστυσλατ в̄ανώστυσλατ в̄ατώστυσλατ в̄ατώστυσλατ в̄ιώστυσλατ),
                   :imperative  => nil,
                   :infinitive  => "μωστυσλώτ",
                   :participle  => "μούστασλατ" }
    - latin = { :present     => %w('āstuslāt tāstuslāt tāstusləthī yāstuslāt yāstusləthī nāstusləthū tāstusləthū tāstusləthū yāstusləthū),
                :preterite   => %w(nistuslāthet nistuslāthətha nistuslāthəčhe nistuslāt nistuslāthā nistuslātnā nistuslāthəthun nistuslāthəčhin nistuslāthū),
                :imperfect   => %w(nistusluot nistusluothat nistusluothaš nistusluot nistusluothā nistusluothan nistusluothəthun nistusluothəčhin nistusluothū),
                :subjunctive => %w(vāstuslət vatāstuslət vatāstuslət vyāstuslət vyāstuslət vanāstuslət vatāstuslət vatāstuslət vyāstuslət),
                :imperative  => nil,
                :infinitive  => "māstuslāt",
                :participle  => "mūstaslət" }
    = render 'full_conjugation_table', :title => "Scale VI Conjugation", :verb => { :ala => "nistuslāt", :eng => "be vanquished" }, :alashian => alashian, :latin => latin

%section.footnotes
  = footnote do
    Despite *wkhād being both a #{template "C1"} glide root and a #{template "C2"} aspirate root, only the former affects its conjugation. Since the monophthongization generated by the initial glide always results in a long vowel preceding #{template "C2"}, the aspirate is deprived of any opportunities to trigger vowel reduction.
